SARS-CoV is highly contagious and must be handled under stringent protection, so we utilized MLV/SARS-CoV pseudotype virus to evaluate 3E8 mAb. MLV pseudotype virus could inherit new cell tropism of envelope protein donating virus [13], [15], [19]. In this study, the genome of MLV was pseudotyped to carried SARS-CoV spike protein and GFP reporter gene. Viral supernatant from transfected 293T cells was concentrated 15-fold to a titer of 7.48 × 104
 IU/ml. MLV/SARS-CoV could infect SARS-CoV-susceptible Vero E6 cells, since giant multinucleated Vero E6 cells with EGFP fluorescence appeared after infection (Fig. 1
). And the titer was also determined by the percentage of GFP-positive Vero E6 after infected.
